  "doc_id": "60690",
  "text": "The results presented have expanded our knowledge on how POL and PLL1 are regulated in planta by showing that these two phosphatases are plasma membrane localized through acylation. This work has also provided evidence of a role for phospholipids, tentatively PI(4)P, in the POL/PLL1-dependent CLE/ WOX signal transduction pathways. Further studies are needed to better understand the precise roles of PI(4)P in regulating these key developmental pathways. These results also contribute to recent literature that has revealed phosphatidylinositol phosphates as key developmental regulators in multicellular organisms [CITATION_1] .",
